div.p: REGNUM (anc. geog.), a town of the Regni, a people in Britain, next the Cantii, now Surry, Suſſex, and the coaſt of Hampſhire, (Camden) ; a town ſituated, by the Itinerary numbers, on the confines of the Belgæ, in a place now called Ringwood, in Hampſhire, on the rivulet Avon, running down from Saliſhury, and about ten miles or more diſtant from the ſea.
